Five people have been confirmed dead while nine others sustained serious injuries in a road accident at Kapiti plains along the Mombasa-Nairobi highway. According to Machakos County Commissioner Abdullahi Galgalo, the accident which occurred today morning involved a church van and a lorry. ALSO READ:

Africa rates highest in road accident deaths: WHO “The accident occurred after a church van that was headed towards Mombasa collided head-on with a truck approaching Nairobi,” he said. The county boss said that the van belongs to a Mombasa based church and its occupants were travelling from a church event that had taken place over the weekend in Siaya County. The deceased were ferried to the Machakos Level 5 hospital mortuary while the injured rushed to hospital for treatment.